{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"generated":true,"title":"How-to Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest"],"anchor":"How-to-Guides"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoimplementservice"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"How to Implement the Service","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Wire "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" into the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" plugin so the store sees real-time entitlement updates from RevenueCat."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide takes you from a wired Swidux app with a paywall slice to a live RevenueCat-backed entitlement pipeline. It covers SDK configuration, plugin registration, observation lifecycle, and refresh\/restore flows."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the API-level reference of the service, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For the entitlement mapping rules, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For the upstream plugin contract — actions, state shape, dispatch semantics — see Swidux’s "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a Paywall"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiduxPaywall Reference"}]},{"type":"text","text":"; this guide does not repeat that material."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Before-you-start","text":"Before you start"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide assumes:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You have a wired Swidux app — ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppAction","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppReducer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" exist, and the store is in the SwiftUI environment.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Your ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" already has a ","type":"text"},{"code":"paywall: PaywallState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" slice and your ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppAction","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has a ","type":"text"},{"code":".paywall(PaywallAction)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" case. If not, follow Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a Paywall","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" guide first.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You have a RevenueCat project, an API key, and at least one entitlement identifier configured in the RevenueCat dashboard."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Add-the-dependencies","text":"Step 1: Add the dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add both Swift packages to your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/HeirloomLogic\/Swidux\", branch: \"main\"),","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/HeirloomLogic\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\", branch: \"main\"),","],"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the products you need to your app target:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".target(","    name: \"MyApp\",","    dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"Swidux\", package: \"Swidux\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxPaywall\", package: \"Swidux\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),","    ]",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is optional — drop it if you don’t need the bundled sheets.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-2-Configure-RevenueCat-at-launch","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Step 2: Configure RevenueCat at launch"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"text":" calls into ","type":"text"},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Configure the SDK before constructing the store:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ MyApp.swift","import RevenueCat","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    @State private var store: AppStore","","    init() {","        Purchases.configure(withAPIKey: \"your_revenuecat_api_key\")","        _store = State(wrappedValue: AppStore.configured())","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup { ContentView().environment(store) }","    }","}"]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" traps if used unconfigured. Configure it before anything that constructs ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", including SwiftUI previews — guard preview-only code with ","type":"text"},{"code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Step-3-Construct-the-service","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Step 3: Construct the service"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create the service with the entitlement identifier you set up in the RevenueCat dashboard:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","let service = RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app sells a separate lifetime SKU alongside a subscription, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the dual-entitlement form."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-4-Register-the-paywall-plugin","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Step 4: Register the paywall plugin"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass the service to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" when wiring the store:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ AppStore.swift","import Swidux","import SwiduxPaywall","import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","extension Store where State == AppState, Action == AppAction {","    static func configured() -> AppStore {","        let plugins = PluginHost<AppState, AppAction>()","","        plugins.register(","            PaywallPlugin<AppState, AppAction>(","                state: \\.paywall,","                action: AppAction.paywall,","                extractAction: { if case .paywall(let a) = $0 { return a }; return nil },","                service: RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")","            )","        )","","        return Store(","            initialState: AppState(),","            reducer: AppReducer().reduce,","            plugins: plugins","        )","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin owns reducing for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall"},{"type":"text","text":" actions; your root reducer should fall through with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"return nil"},{"text":" for that case.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Step 5: Observe customer info on launch","anchor":"Step-5-Observe-customer-info-on-launch","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Start the entitlement stream once, on the root view:"}]},{"code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @Environment(AppStore.self) private var store","","    var body: some View {","        RootContent()","            .task { store.send(.paywall(.observeCustomerInfo)) }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" returns a long-lived effect that consumes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService.customerInfoStream()"},{"type":"text","text":". Every snapshot the service yields flows through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".customerInfoUpdated"},{"type":"text","text":" and updates "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isPro"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"},{"type":"text","text":". The effect lives for the duration of the stream, so the store stays in sync with RevenueCat without polling."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-6-Gate-features","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Step 6: Gate features"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isGateSatisfied"},{"type":"text","text":" before running gated work. If it’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", dispatch "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".request(reason:)"},{"type":"text","text":" instead:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Button(\"Export PDF\") {","    if store.paywall.isGateSatisfied {","        store.send(.export(.exportPDF))","    } else {","        store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"export-pdf\")))","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isGateSatisfied"},{"type":"text","text":" returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" when the user holds an active pro subscription "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"or"}]},{"type":"text","text":" a permanent license — feature code does not need to know which."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-7-Wire-the-UI","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Step 7: Wire the UI"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To present "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" and the customer center, attach the bundled sheets to a root view. See "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 8: Restore purchases","anchor":"Step-8-Restore-purchases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a restore button to your paywall UI. Reflect "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isLoading"},{"type":"text","text":" to disable it while the call is in flight:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Button(\"Restore Purchases\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.restorePurchases))","}",".disabled(store.paywall.isLoading)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The plugin calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService.restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":", which forwards to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared.restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":". On success the resulting snapshot flows through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".customerInfoUpdated"},{"type":"text","text":" and updates the gate. On failure, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.error"},{"type":"text","text":" is set."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 9: Handle errors","anchor":"Step-9-Handle-errors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The service throws whatever "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":" throws — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ErrorCode.networkError"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".offlineConnectionError"},{"type":"text","text":", configuration errors, etc. The plugin catches the error and dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed(message)"},{"type":"text","text":". Read "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.error"},{"type":"text","text":" from your paywall view to surface a retry affordance:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["if let error = store.paywall.error {","    Text(error)","        .foregroundStyle(.red)","    Button(\"Retry\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.refreshCustomerInfo))","    }","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/ServiceReference":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/servicereference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"API reference for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"text":" — the RevenueCat-backed ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"text":" conformer that the paywall plugin consumes.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","title":"Service Reference"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToAddAPermanentLicense":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Sell a lifetime entitlement alongside a subscription and surface both flags through the paywall plugin.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","title":"How to Add a Permanent License","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoaddapermanentlicense"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPreviewAndTest":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopreviewandtest","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Drive entitlement state from SwiftUI previews and tests with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" — no RevenueCat SDK call required."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest","role":"article","title":"How to Preview and Test"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"text":". Implements ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"text":" against ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" for drop-in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"text":" presentation.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","role":"collection","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Attach ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallSheet"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterSheet"},{"type":"text","text":" from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" to a root view, driven by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","role":"article","title":"How to Present the UI"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/EntitlementMapping":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/entitlementmapping","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How RevenueCat’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerInfo.entitlements"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to Swidux’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","role":"article","title":"Entitlement Mapping"}}}